1
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:16,120
LET'S HAVE SOME NOODLES

2
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,040
Taew.

3
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:27,320
We have to settle
Dad's medical bills in two days.

4
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,240
How much is left?

5
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:30,800
We're five thousand short
of thirty thousand.

6
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:33,680
I'll get paid
for the queuing job in two days.

7
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,600
I should get around three thousand or so.

8
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:37,320
Still two thousand short.

9
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,480
Anything we can pawn right now?

10
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:53,080
No, Sis. This is really important to me.

11
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,840
It's not just Dad's medical bills.

12
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:58,120
There's also our living expenses, right?

13
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,960
Plus the two million we owe Kamnan Danai.

14
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:01,200
Where are we gonna get the money?

15
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,440
Ting.

16
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:04,720
Let's save money wherever we can.

17
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:07,360
I know how much the internet costs.
I'm the one paying for it.

18
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:09,240
What else do you want me to cut back on?

19
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,720
I'm already saving all I can.

20
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:15,040
I don't have
a single valuable thing on me.

21
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,800
My friends all have nice things.

22
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:19,280
Why are you comparing yourself
to other people, Ting?

23
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,800
I'm not comparing anything.

24
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,040
What she said was right.

25
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,680
Our life is fine just the way it is.

26
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,280
No need to follow every trend.

27
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:32,400
I'm not following anyone.

28
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,200
I completely understand.

29
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:36,280
I just wants us
to finally get out of this mess.

30
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:37,960
Ting.

31
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,800
Ting.

32
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:50,520
Thank you.

33
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,720
50,000 BAHT

34
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:58,840
Well… Right now,
I only have thirty thousand.

35
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,320
May I pay this amount for now?

36
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,760
I'll add the rest to next week's payment.

37
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,800
Please. I'm begging you.

38
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:07,720
Please help us.

39
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,040
I promise something like this
won't happen again.

40
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:12,760
I promise I'll definitely
find the money to pay you.

41
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,800
I can cover
the remaining twenty thousand for you.

42
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,840
Pay me back whenever you can.

43
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:20,320
It's okay.
I'll find a way to pay for it myself.

44
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,360
Taew.

45
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:25,360
Right now,
Dad's life is the most important thing.

46
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,120
Think it through.

47
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:31,760
Mom.
I don't want to owe anyone a favor.

48
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,400
All done.

49
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:44,200
If you're uneasy about this,
may I have your LINE ID?

50
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:48,480
That way, I can send you the receipt

51
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,120
for the transfer I made.

52
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:52,360
So you'll know
you're borrowing money from me.

53
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:55,440
I charge 12% interest per year,

54
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,840
which is within the legal limit.

55
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,960
Taew, Kamnan Danai's here.

56
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,280
Wait.

57
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:27,800
- Hey, let's talk about the land.
- I have an urgent matter to attend to.

58
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,800
- Hey, hey.
- Let's go.

59
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,120
- Hello, Sir.
- Hello.

60
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:43,760
Wow, I'm a big fan of yours.

61
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:48,000
Can I take a pic with you?
I want to show it to my dad.

62
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,080
Of course.

63
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,400
- That's it.
- Okay.

64
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:55,120
Thank you very much.
I'm definitely voting for you.

65
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,080
Thank you so much.

66
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:58,360
Well, I'll be excusing myself then.

67
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,600
Alright.

68
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:08,400
Where are you two rushing off to?

69
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,920
I just went to check on Mr. Chalit.

70
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,200
He doesn't seem to be getting any better.

71
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,320
My dad had brain surgery,

72
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,640
not an appendectomy,
so he needs time to recover.

73
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:30,720
That's right.

74
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,400
That's why it's worrying.

75
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,240
Because the medical expenses

76
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:39,360
would probably be very high
if he has to stay for a long time.

77
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:42,040
How are you going to pay me back then?

78
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:47,880
Can I postpone the payment, please?

79
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:49,920
Right now, I really don't have any money.

80
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,640
Then sell the land.

81
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:55,240
If you sell the land,
everything will be settled.

82
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:58,000
The lion dance troupe is done for anyway.

83
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,320
How is it going to bring in any money?

84
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,800
Or…

85
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,800
You still have the lion head, right?

86
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:08,000
So one of you holds the head,
and the other holds the tail.

87
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:12,400
Then you hold out a bowl
and beg for money.

88
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,840
Maybe you'll get enough
to pay off my interest.

89
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:17,160
- You…
- Taew.

90
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:26,520
- <i>Are you Mr. Chalit Kaenthaisong's family?</i>
- Yes.

91
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:29,320
- <i>The doctor wants to see you urgently.</i>
- Yes. I'll be right there.

92
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,440
I hope it's good news.

93
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,880
Thank you for your advice.

94
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,680
Let's go, Mom.

95
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:03,080
Today, I need to place
a central line in his neck vein

96
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,600
to administer his medication.

97
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,960
The veins in his arms
are becoming inflamed.

98
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:10,960
But there's still a chance
he'll wake up, right?

99
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:15,000
After the surgery,
we hope the patient will wake up.

100
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:17,320
But if he doesn't,
it will become critical.

101
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Taew.

102
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,040
If Dad…

103
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,640
Calm down, Mom.
Dad will wake up.

104
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,080
I have to be honest with you.

105
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:41,280
After some time,

106
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:44,080
if he still doesn't respond
or can't breathe on his own,

107
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:46,960
I will have to ask the family to decide

108
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:50,240
whether to perform CPR
or let him pass away peacefully.

109
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:03,360
Doctor, please help my dad.

110
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:06,040
Please take care of him.

111
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,080
Oh, please.

112
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,560
I almost ran into Kamnan Danai.

113
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,960
Thank you so much
for stepping in for me, Wat.

114
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,640
That wore me out, Boss.

115
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,360
But judging by the way
Ms. Taew and her mom act,

116
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,600
they don't want to meet the Kamnan.

117
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,960
Wat, do you think…

118
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:44,520
they know the one
who's been buying up all this land

119
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,960
is the Kamnan, not Ms. Ploy?

120
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:51,520
Didn't you say
you'd take care of Mr. Chalit's land?

121
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,120
I heard that his wife and kids
still won't sell the land?

122
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,720
At this rate, when are we
ever going to start our project?

123
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,560
I'm working on it.

124
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:03,280
Actually, there are
a few plots of land by the river,

125
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,920
right next to the shrine.

126
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,480
- I think I'll try--
- I bought up all the land around there.

127
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:10,440
I won't accept it.
If you do that, I'm done for.

128
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,920
There's no point looking at other land.

129
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,040
The Singaporean company
investing with us has settled

130
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,040
on that plot of land,

131
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,400
because the master said that

132
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,720
the feng shui is very good
next to the ancient shrine.

133
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:23,160
That's right.
The master also mentioned that

134
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,560
the shrine over there

135
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:27,440
must be facing a good direction,
or at a good angle.

136
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:29,600
That's why people keep coming to pray.

137
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,920
The auspicious star, or the wealth star,

138
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,680
has to be located in the front.

139
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:36,280
As for the river, it creates movement

140
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:39,640
that keeps the wealth star
activated all the time.

141
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,320
Good feng shui like this

142
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,160
isn't easy to find, you know.

143
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,080
Yes.

144
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:46,640
Then please get this taken care of,
Ms. Ploy.

145
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,680
I will.

146
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,440
Actually,
if we had done it my way from the start,

147
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:53,600
you probably would've gotten
the land already.

148
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:09,200
<i>Holy Lord, what should I do?</i>

149
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:11,280
<i>How am I going to afford Dad's treatment?</i>

150
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,760
<i>Plus, we owe Kamnan Danai</i>
<i>another two million.</i>

151
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:16,000
<i>I've tried doing everything I can,</i>

152
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:18,320
<i>but I still can't earn enough money.</i>

153
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:21,120
<i>No one has hired our lion dance troupe</i>

154
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,960
<i>since I broke the drum that day.</i>

155
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:26,200
<i>I still can't figure out</i>
<i>what I should do to find a way out.</i>

156
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:33,960
Taew.

157
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,400
Oh, Sai?

158
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:41,360
What's with you today?
Why the lion dance practice?

159
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:45,240
Just to relieve stress.
I don't have any gigs right now.

160
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,600
Then keep practicing.

161
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:19,160
<i>Cast away sorrow and grief</i>

162
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:22,320
<i>Come out and dance</i>

163
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:26,720
<i>Let go of your sorrow</i>

164
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:32,680
<i>Forget about love, don't worry about it</i>

165
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:37,120
<i>Just a partner</i>
<i>You'll find someone new in time</i>

166
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:42,960
<i>But the joy inside our hearts…</i>

167
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:49,080
<i>Is dancing to the Mor Lam beat</i>

168
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:07,160
<i>Cast away sorrow and grief</i>

169
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:11,040
<i>Come out and dance, let go of your sorrow</i>

170
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:14,200
<i>Forget about love, don't worry about it</i>

171
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:16,800
<i>Just a partner</i>
<i>You'll find someone new in time</i>

172
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:20,080
<i>But the joy inside our hearts</i>

173
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:24,560
<i>Is dancing to the Mor Lam beat</i>

174
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:28,200
<i>Wherever the festival is</i>
<i>As long as I can hear the music</i>

175
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:30,400
<i>Through the thunder and the rain…</i>

176
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:34,200
<i>I never back down</i>

177
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:37,040
<i>Single ladies never get tired of Mor Lam</i>

178
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:39,720
<i>Mor Lam plays</i>
<i>And even the elders get up to dance</i>

179
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,960
<i>Tired of rolling out their mats</i>

180
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,840
<i>As the dust comes swirling up!</i>

181
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:48,680
<i>Oh! Up, up, up goes the dust!</i>

182
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,080
I've got an idea.

183
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,360
I'm going to mix
the lion dance with <i>Mor Lam</i>.

184
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:10,840
<i>Mor Lam Sing</i> Lion Dance!

185
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,720
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

186
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,520
Everyone's here, Taew.

187
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:26,280
I've decided. I'm going to
perform the lion dance myself.

188
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:30,160
Ugh, ever since I was born,

189
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:32,760
I've never seen a woman do it.

190
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:35,680
Well, we have to do something new.

191
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:36,800
No need to be like others.

192
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,520
Let's do something nobody else is doing.

193
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:42,600
We have to take risks in life.
If we don't try, we won't know.

194
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:46,320
Yeah. We'll never know if it'll work

195
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,720
unless we try, right?

196
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:53,720
But I know you only learned
the lion dance by watching others.

197
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:56,080
You've never actually done it for real.

198
00:13:57,160 --> 00:14:00,000
I didn't say I'd do it like Dad.

199
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:02,520
But I'll perform it to <i>Mor Lam</i> music.

200
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:05,200
Oh my goodness.

201
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:07,040
This is getting out of hand.

202
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:10,200
Doing a lion dance to <i>Mor Lam</i>?

203
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:13,560
That's going to be a total mismatch.

204
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:16,560
Right, Old Man Kamphoon?

205
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,640
But I think Taew makes a good point.

206
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:24,120
We Isan people
came to live with the lion troupe.

207
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:27,400
Both of those things
are part of who we are.

208
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:30,680
So we have to show who we really are.

209
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:35,560
Uncle, you still don't know
what it's going to be like.

210
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:38,280
Just watch. We'll show you in a moment.

211
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:42,120
Watch this. You guys are gonna be amazed.

212
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:44,520
Amazed?

213
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:56,440
<i>Are the girls ready? Are the divas ready?</i>

214
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:59,920
<i>Single people, move over here…</i>

215
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:03,320
<i>Time to get down!</i>

216
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:13,240
<i>Dance, dance, dance!</i>
<i>Miss Mor Lam, go dance, dance, dance!</i>

217
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:16,760
<i>Don't be down about your life</i>

218
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:19,400
<i>The stage is packed, crowded, crowded</i>

219
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:22,800
<i>Let's forget the one who left us</i>

220
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:26,160
<i>Dancing in the dust, not giving a damn</i>

221
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:29,080
<i>Shaking by the stage</i>
<i>Making no trouble at all</i>

222
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:35,720
<i>New era girls, all about that good time!</i>

223
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:01,400
Great!

224
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:11,840
Really beautiful.

225
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:15,200
- That works.
- Yeah.

226
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:22,680
Why are you here again?
Do you need something else from me?

227
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:28,160
I came to warn you about Ms. Ploy.

228
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:32,400
Warn me? Aren't you working with her?

229
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:34,640
And Ms. Ploy is buying up all this land

230
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:37,080
because your company
is building a shopping mall, right?

231
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:39,880
Yes.

232
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:42,200
But I never
intended to force you to sell it.

233
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,200
I'm worried that Ms. Ploy

234
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:46,920
is going to use violence again.

235
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:50,480
Let her try. Someone like me
isn't afraid of anything anyway.

236
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:55,320
I know you're strong.

237
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:57,960
But you're still a woman.

238
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:08,839
What are you doing?

239
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,480
I just saw some dust in her hair.

240
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:26,680
Thank you for warning us about Ms. Ploy.

241
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:29,880
But don't worry. I'm a boxer.

242
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,480
I can take care of Taew.

243
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:35,360
You should leave.

244
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:37,680
We still don't trust any of you.

245
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,520
Tawat.

246
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:49,880
Have you seen the clip I sent you?

247
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:52,320
Create a dummy account
and post this clip for me.

248
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:55,760
And add the hashtag
#FemaleLionDancer for me, too.

249
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:59,040
Mr. Natee.

250
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,040
Hello.

251
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:05,040
Do you remember me? My name is Ting.

252
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:08,480
I'm Taew's younger brother.
We met at the hospital.

253
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:09,960
Of course, Ting.

254
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,720
So… what's going on?

255
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,520
Well…

256
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:17,680
I'd really like to sell the land.

257
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:22,320
I want to make money
so I can get Dad better treatment.

258
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,960
But no one at home is willing to sell it.

259
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:27,680
Your sister won't sell it, right?

260
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:31,400
Or… does she think
she has other ways to make money?

261
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:34,200
I really don't know.

262
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:36,040
She has her ego.

263
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,760
She probably thinks she can do anything.

264
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:43,880
Hear me out, Ting.

265
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,040
About the hospital,

266
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:48,840
- I happen to know some great neurologists.
- Yes.

267
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:51,520
If your family
doesn't mind me stepping in,

268
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,480
I can contact them.

269
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:55,560
Not at all, Mr. Natee.

270
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,680
Then…

271
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,960
I'll talk Mom
into selling the land to you.

272
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,200
Talking to Taew will be difficult.

273
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:03,400
You probably
wouldn't disobey Dad's orders.

274
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:06,440
And you would?

275
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:10,680
Of course. I'm Dad's son too.

276
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:12,760
No matter what,
half of this house is mine.

277
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,640
And if I want to sell the land,

278
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,280
I'm doing it for Dad too.

279
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,400
STERILE AREA
STAFF ONLY

280
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:56,080
Dad, I brought Grandpa to you,

281
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:59,200
so he can protect you,
and you can get well soon.

282
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,480
Dear.

283
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:18,840
Even though our troupe
doesn't have any work,

284
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:22,080
Taew isn't just
sitting around doing nothing.

285
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:25,720
Yes, Dad.

286
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:27,720
Right now, the troupe and I

287
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,440
are coming up with
<i>Mor Lam Sing</i> Lion Dance.

288
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,320
I need you to be my strength right now.

289
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:35,360
Please let
the <i>Mor Lam Sing</i> Lion Dance be a success.

290
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:53,120
Taew!

291
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:56,040
- What's up, Sai?
- Come check this out.

292
00:20:58,160 --> 00:20:59,200
What is it?

293
00:20:59,280 --> 00:21:02,680
Wait, why the full makeup?
Aren't you going to sleep?

294
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:05,760
Forget my face for now. Here.

295
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:14,720
LION DANCE

296
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:18,160
Someone filmed us doing the lion dance
to <i>Mor Lam</i> and posted it on TikTok.

297
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,160
Female lion dancers?

298
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,400
Who filmed this?

299
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:25,600
I don't know.
It's a new account that was just created.

300
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:27,800
Well…

301
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:34,720
But this was filmed

302
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:38,000
from around the bridge
that connects to the shrine.

303
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,280
When we were rehearsing,
we were all in the courtyard, right?

304
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:48,800
Really beautiful.

305
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:52,000
- That works.
- Yeah.

306
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:57,240
Hey, why are you smiling?

307
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,520
You know who filmed it?

308
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,160
I'm just happy about the likes.

309
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:02,920
How would I know who it was?

310
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,720
Maybe it was someone who came to pray,

311
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,080
heard us, and walked over to watch.

312
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:11,360
Just walked over to watch?

313
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:12,920
But it got so many views.

314
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:15,280
If people actually meant to watch it,
the views would be insane.

315
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:18,600
Well, you can promote it more.

316
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:19,800
Sure.

317
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:21,680
I'm sharing it.

318
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:22,800
Let me see.

319
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:25,520
Wow, we're going viral.

320
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:32,480
- What are you doing?
- I should be the one asking.

321
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,160
Unbelievable.

322
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,520
I found this clip of the girls.

323
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:39,120
What does that have to do with me?

324
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,680
The girls doing lion dance.

325
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:44,080
It's your sister. It has hundreds
of thousands of views. Someone shared it.

326
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:45,040
Here, watch.

327
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:48,120
- Who's that?
- It's Sai. Look.

328
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,280
Let me see.

329
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:51,320
It really is her.

330
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:54,880
My channel's gonna go viral now. Come on.

331
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:06,440
Aek.

332
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:08,720
What are you watching?
You're laughing like a fool.

333
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:12,200
It's the lion dance video, Grandma.
Didn't you see it?

334
00:23:12,280 --> 00:23:14,800
- I'm seeing it now.
- Then why are you asking?

335
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,960
Are you trying to mess with me?

336
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:22,160
MOR LAM SING LION DANCE

337
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:23,280
Hey.

338
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:25,720
Look at these female lion dancers.
So cool.

339
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,920
Huh? Let me see.

340
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:30,000
Wow, they're dancing
to <i>Mor Lam</i> music, too.

341
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:32,040
That's funny. Look.

342
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:33,120
But they're so cool.

343
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,920
I guess no one's booking them anymore,

344
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:44,640
so they're dancing the lion
to <i>Mor Lam</i> music.

345
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:45,720
That's good.

346
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:49,560
Then make sure they run out of ways
to make a living soon.

347
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:51,840
I want to see

348
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,800
how long they're going
to starve themselves

349
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:56,280
in the house they love so dearly.

350
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:57,960
Of course, Kamnan.

351
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:01,160
But please hurry up. If Natee

352
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:03,800
convinces the Singaporeans
to buy different land,

353
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:05,240
I'll lose hundreds of millions.

354
00:24:06,080 --> 00:24:10,160
The chairman said
they've already looked at a lot of places.

355
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:12,200
But they haven't found
a single plot they like.

356
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:13,600
No matter what,

357
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:17,000
the chairman won't let
this plot of land slip through our hands.

358
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:19,920
But if Natee
successfully lobbies the Singaporeans,

359
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,000
the chairman will trust his son anyway.

360
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:25,280
He loves his son.

361
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:27,120
And if that happens,

362
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:31,320
Natee will be sitting
in the executive chair before we know it.

363
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:32,560
Won't we all be screwed?

364
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:37,480
Okay.
I'll take care of it for you.

365
00:24:58,280 --> 00:25:00,560
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

366
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:15,160
Taew.

367
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:18,880
Taew!

368
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:26,640
Huh? Old Man.

369
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:28,520
Why did you turn it off?

370
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:32,280
I'm telling you straight.

371
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:34,200
I'm a real Isan man.

372
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:35,880
And I can't accept

373
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:39,360
the fact that you're mixing
the lion dance with <i>Mor Lam Sing</i>.

374
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:41,960
No one does that.
It would ruin the troupe's reputation.

375
00:25:43,160 --> 00:25:46,080
In lion dancing,
the head and the tail move

376
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:47,920
and step in sync.

377
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:50,920
The head and the tail
have to breathe together.

378
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,320
Do everything at the same time,

379
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:55,600
- as if they're the exact same person.
- Ugh, Old Man.

380
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,040
I'm still looking for someone.

381
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,400
Plus, everyone respects you too much.

382
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,280
So no one will be the tail for me.

383
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:08,480
"To each their own.

384
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:12,560
If the crow doesn't like the ocean,
then so be it."

385
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:15,440
- That means…
- Don't you dare blame me.

386
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:18,080
Let me tell you.

387
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:21,080
You have to find someone
who's willing to be

388
00:26:21,160 --> 00:26:22,600
your jittery and clumsy tail.

389
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:24,040
This kind of dance,

390
00:26:24,120 --> 00:26:26,440
if someone's willing to do it,
then you can rehearse.

391
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:29,040
If you can't find someone,
I say you should give up

392
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:30,600
on your "<i>Mor Lam Sing</i> Lion Dance."

393
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:34,880
Focus on your other work

394
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:37,720
and earn money to treat your father.

395
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:45,800
Let's continue.

396
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:55,120
The tire is flat.

397
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:56,200
Hey!

398
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:57,400
What are you lot doing here?!

399
00:26:57,480 --> 00:27:00,240
If you want to eat feet,
we don't sell them here.

400
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:01,320
Really?

401
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:03,400
What is this?

402
00:27:03,480 --> 00:27:05,280
What the hell are you doing?

403
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,920
Hey!

404
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,440
- What the hell's going on?
- You!

405
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:12,240
Hey!

406
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:14,960
Do you even know who I am?

407
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:16,600
Hey, you!

408
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:20,040
Hey.

409
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,200
Old Man.

410
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:27,480
Come on.

411
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:34,360
- Damn you, little kid!
- Let him go!

412
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:39,200
Taew.

413
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:42,440
Take that!

414
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:44,320
Stop!

415
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:46,320
Police! Stop fighting!

416
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:51,880
You bastards.

417
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:56,600
Are you okay?

418
00:27:57,840 --> 00:27:58,720
Officer.

419
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,920
Please arrest all of them, Officer.

420
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,560
- Taew.
- Mom. Are you okay?

421
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:04,680
Are you hurt?

422
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:05,680
Taew.

423
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:09,760
Officer, arrest these thugs right away.

424
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:12,040
Arrest them all. Do it.

425
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:23,080
What? How could we
possibly be in the wrong?

426
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:25,640
I only sent my men to collect your debt.

427
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:28,280
But you all beat them almost to death.

428
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:30,800
Right now, the doctor
hasn't discharged them yet.

429
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:33,640
So how can you say you're not at fault?

430
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,480
Watch your mouth.

431
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:39,280
Your men came to attack us first.

432
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:40,440
We were defending ourselves.

433
00:28:41,280 --> 00:28:42,440
Defending yourselves?

434
00:28:43,040 --> 00:28:44,520
My guys went to
collect the debt peacefully.

435
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:46,920
But you turned it into a scene

436
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:49,520
by knocking over carts
and throwing things around,

437
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:52,240
then you accused my men of doing it.

438
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:53,480
How could you do that?

439
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:56,320
Wow, you liar--

440
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,360
Sai, shut up.

441
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:01,240
I'm sorry.

442
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:05,920
Debt? What debt?

443
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:07,280
What do I owe you?

444
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:09,520
It's your debt to Kamnan Danai.

445
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:18,440
He assigned my company
to collect the debt.

446
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:25,600
No wonder you're rich,

447
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,000
and have no conscience.

448
00:29:27,080 --> 00:29:28,760
- Kamnan Danai is backing you.
- Hey.

449
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:30,960
If you owe money, you have to pay it.

450
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:32,640
Why make all these excuses?

451
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:35,120
- Hey.
- Don't pick a fight with me.

452
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:40,960
Okay, but debt collection

453
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:43,440
has to follow the legal process.

454
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:45,840
No matter how important you are,

455
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:47,560
you still don't have the right to intrude,

456
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:50,240
destroy stuff,
and make all sorts of demands

457
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:52,240
until a pot lid
hit me in the face like this.

458
00:29:52,320 --> 00:29:54,240
Don't mention others,

459
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:55,920
or you'll get sued in another case.

460
00:29:56,840 --> 00:29:57,920
Get sued?

461
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,600
They bullied us first,

462
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:01,320
so we were just defending ourselves.

463
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:03,960
If you don't believe me,
you can check the surveillance cameras.

464
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:05,320
You'll see it with your own eyes.

465
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:07,800
But right now, you are suspects

466
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:11,240
because you started a fight
and assaulted them.

467
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:30,080
- Officer, you can't do this.
- Come with me.

468
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,920
- They're innocent, Officer.
- Hey!

469
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:35,080
- Is there any justice in the world?
- No!

470
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:37,320
- Taew.
- There is no justice in the world.

471
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:39,960
Please don't do this, Officer.

472
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:41,160
No, Officer.

473
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:43,840
- Officer. Officer.
- Taew!

474
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:44,880
Officer.

475
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:51,040
Where are you, Natee?

476
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:54,400
Calm down, Ting. I'm on my way.

477
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:55,680
Alright.

478
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:59,200
Taew.

479
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:01,600
Officer, she hasn't done anything wrong.

480
00:31:01,680 --> 00:31:02,920
Please release her.

481
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:04,280
- Officer.
- Release her.

482
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:06,680
- Officer. Officer.
- Officer.

483
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:08,360
Why did you arrest
Old Man Kamphoon and Taew?

484
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:09,680
Why didn't you arrest Kamnan's men?

485
00:31:09,760 --> 00:31:11,160
Stay out of this,

486
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:13,680
or I'll arrest you too.

487
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:15,880
Why should I?

488
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:17,760
Huh?

489
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:19,240
You brought in innocent people!

490
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:20,840
Big mouth, huh?

491
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,720
Sergeant, arrest him too!

492
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:25,880
Let's go.

493
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:26,880
- Officer.
- Kla.

494
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:29,360
- A cop like you should protect people.
- Kla!

495
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:31,360
- Kla!
- Kla.

496
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:32,800
- Kla, no!
- Take care of the people!

497
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,720
- Easy, Kla!
- Let go of me!

498
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:36,200
Arrest him!

499
00:31:36,280 --> 00:31:37,880
Kla, calm down.

500
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,080
Let go!

501
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:42,280
Hey!

502
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:45,120
Guys, look at this.

503
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:47,720
- We're innocent, but they arrested us.
- Stop filming!

504
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:49,560
- We're innocent.
- Why are you filming?

505
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:50,720
Don't touch my daughter.

506
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:53,480
She's a bold-faced liar.
Everyone, remember her face.

507
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:56,120
She sent people to harass us,
and yet she gets away with it.

508
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:58,080
Look at her. It's this bitch.

509
00:31:58,160 --> 00:32:01,400
- Remember her face.
- Sai, stop. Stop filming.

510
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:03,760
Sergeant, take them away.

511
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:06,040
- Hey, go on!
- Taew.

512
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:07,520
Let me go!

513
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:08,560
Please let Taew go.

514
00:32:08,640 --> 00:32:10,520
- Please release her.
- Take them inside.

515
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:11,440
- Get in.
- Let go!

516
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:13,400
- Let me go!
- Officer.

517
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:16,240
- Hey!
- Come here.

518
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:22,040
Ms. Ploy.

519
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:26,720
Please don't hold this against Taew.

520
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:31,240
If we let things go on like this,
my life will be in danger, won't it?

521
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:34,360
I don't want to wake up
in the middle of the night,

522
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:37,640
fearing your daughter
will sneak in with a knife to my throat.

523
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:43,160
She wouldn't do that.

524
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:45,000
I can guarantee it.

525
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,720
What do you want me to do?

526
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:51,240
I'll do anything, Ms. Ploy.

527
00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:53,400
Then sell the land to me.

528
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:56,640
Mom, don't listen to her.

529
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:57,720
- Mom.
- Aunt Yao.

530
00:32:57,800 --> 00:32:59,720
- Don't listen to her.
- It's no use.

531
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:07,920
I can't sell you the land, Ms. Ploy.

532
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:12,200
In that case,
I can't help you with anything either.

533
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:19,320
Tonight, your daughter
will probably have to sleep in jail.

534
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:25,760
Ms. Ploy,

535
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:28,080
I'm begging you.

536
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:32,640
- If you want me to bow to you, I will.
- Mom.

537
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:38,320
Yao. Don't do it, Yao.

538
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:45,240
Mom, don't bow to her.

539
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:02,800
- Mom.
- Aunt Yao.

540
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:04,440
Don't bow to her.

541
00:34:05,040 --> 00:34:06,920
- Aunt Yao.
- Mom!

542
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:22,560
What a waste, bowing to scum.

543
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:36,120
Please get up, Auntie.

544
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:41,920
Get up, Auntie.

545
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:57,480
I know you sent men
to pick a fight with them first.

546
00:34:57,560 --> 00:34:59,520
Even though
the police helped you cover up,

547
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:01,360
don't think I don't know.

548
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:05,280
The chairman told me
to close this job quickly.

549
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:06,720
You heard that too, right?

550
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:10,560
I think, for the benefit of the company,

551
00:35:10,640 --> 00:35:12,800
you should just
turn a blind eye this time.

552
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:15,520
It's more for your own benefit.

553
00:35:16,120 --> 00:35:17,200
You probably think

554
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:19,080
closing the deal on the land
would be the end of it.

555
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:21,360
But if this story becomes public,

556
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,040
my company's reputation will be damaged.

557
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:25,600
And who knows?
The investors from Singapore

558
00:35:26,240 --> 00:35:28,040
might even terminate the contract.

559
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:30,560
If it comes to that,

560
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:33,600
I guess I'll really have to
find another piece of land.

561
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:35,680
And by then,

562
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:38,040
you'll be the one in trouble,

563
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:41,600
because I'm sure
Kamnan Danai won't take it well.

564
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:58,400
Mr. Natee.

565
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,640
Thank you so much for your help.

566
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:04,640
Otherwise, Ms. Ploy
wouldn't have backed down so easily.

567
00:36:05,720 --> 00:36:08,080
As for your thanks, I'll accept it.

568
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:12,280
Ms. Ploy's case may end today,

569
00:36:12,360 --> 00:36:13,880
because if she continues the lawsuit,

570
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:15,920
she'll lose for trespassing.

571
00:36:17,560 --> 00:36:19,200
But what are you going to do next?

572
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:21,360
There's still Kamnan Danai.

573
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:27,160
I'm thinking about how to handle it.

574
00:36:32,160 --> 00:36:33,280
Please think it through.

575
00:36:35,080 --> 00:36:36,240
You're not alone in this.

576
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:42,360
Please excuse me.

577
00:36:50,760 --> 00:36:52,360
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

578
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:53,720
I knew it.

579
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:56,920
There had to be someone higher up,
like Kamnan Danai, backing them.

580
00:36:57,520 --> 00:36:59,160
Otherwise, they wouldn't dare harm us.

581
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:01,400
They cut off all our sources of income,

582
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:04,800
just so we couldn't pay
for Uncle Lit's treatment.

583
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:08,720
But in the end, she will force
Aunt Yao and Taew to sell the land.

584
00:37:10,480 --> 00:37:12,520
I'll get everyone through this.

585
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:15,600
I won't let the Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe
go bankrupt.

586
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:17,040
I'm going to find clients myself.

587
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:21,480
Who'd support
your <i>Mor Lam Sing</i> Lion Dance, Taew?

588
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:23,920
It's only going to make things worse.

589
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:27,240
I know you don't like
the <i>Mor Lam Sing</i> Lion Dance.

590
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:30,520
But since no one's hiring us
for traditional lion dance anymore,

591
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:33,200
we'll have to take our chances
with the <i>Mor Lam Sing</i> Lion Dance.

592
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:35,520
Yeah, I agree.

593
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:38,200
I won't let the Kimhan Troupe fall apart.

594
00:37:39,160 --> 00:37:41,960
We have to help Uncle Lit
to repay Old Man Liang's kindness.

595
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:45,480
All of us here
will help Taew find the money

596
00:37:46,320 --> 00:37:47,760
by doing the <i>Mor Lam Sing</i> Lion Dance.

597
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,360
We won't let you fight alone, Taew.

598
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:57,040
I promise I'll restore the Kimhan Troupe

599
00:37:57,120 --> 00:37:58,840
to its former glory.

600
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:01,520
Old Man.

601
00:38:03,680 --> 00:38:05,040
Do you believe in me?

602
00:38:09,280 --> 00:38:11,840
<i>Come on now, let's go!</i>

603
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:13,960
<i>Come on, girl! Let's go, let's go!</i>

604
00:38:17,080 --> 00:38:19,400
- Okay, Old Man?
- Let's do it.

605
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:20,560
It's going to be fun.

606
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:24,040
Alright.

607
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:27,000
Maybe it really could be fun,
like you guys said.

608
00:38:29,200 --> 00:38:31,640
<i>Once the curtain rises</i>

609
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:33,360
<i>The curtain</i>

610
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:39,200
<i>This Mor Lam girl will bring the fun</i>

611
00:38:39,280 --> 00:38:43,480
<i>Calling all young men and women</i>

612
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:48,440
<i>Come dance by the stage</i>

613
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:13,320
Subtitle translation by:
Anan Pratchayakul
